        <header class="article-header">
         <h1 class="article-title">
          These Parents Have Every Right To Be Angry, But Not For The Reason The Teacher Thinks.
         </h1>
         <time class="article-date" datetime="2015-04-23">
          POSTED 2 mnths
         </time>
        </header>
        <div class="article-block">
         <div class="article-html">
          <p>
           <img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64,"/>
           <br/>
           <br/>
           Many of us, during our time in school, have encountered teachers who made mistakes in class and viewed corrections from students not as opportunities to learn something themselves, but as unwarranted and intolerable challenges to their authority.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           This teacher, however, took things too far when he sent this letter home to one student that
           <em>
            did
           </em>
           correct him.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="article-block">
         <img alt="..." class="feature-image" src="http://images1.tickld.com/live/articles/a_1554_20150423083529.jpg"/>
        </div>
        <div class="article-block">
         <h3>
          Was this teacher wrong? Share this by clicking below.
         </h3>
        </div>

    /**
     * Check if element is visible in scroll (or exists at all)
     * @param elem
     * @returns {boolean}
     */
    function in_scroll(elem){

        if(!$(elem).length){
            return false;
        }

        var doc_top = $(window).scrollTop();
        var doc_bottom = doc_top + $(window).height();

        var elem_top = $(elem).offset().top;
        var elem_bottom = elem_top + $(elem).height();

        return ((elem_bottom &lt;= doc_bottom) &amp;&amp; (elem_top &gt;= doc_top));
    }

    /**
     * Build initial infinite scroll
     */
    function setup_scroll(){
        $(document).scroll(function(e){
            if(in_scroll(".infinite-scroll-trigger")){
                $(document).unbind('scroll'); // kill off the scroll trigger to stop repeats
                ga('send', 'event', 'articles', 'scroll', 'article', scroll_step);
                $.get('/scroll/article?ref=' + article_ref + "&amp;step=" + scroll_step + "&amp;offset=" + offset,function(response){
                    // remove any existing desktop triggers so we don't hit it again
                    $('.infinite-scroll-trigger').remove();
                    // place new html in the holder
                    $('.infinite-scroll-after').replaceWith(response);
                    scroll_step ++;
                    setup_scroll();
                });
            }
        });
    }

    setup_scroll();
